rComments: Very nice and funny prof who definitely tries to make her lectures interesting to students! She is clearly knowledgeable on the subject and wants to see her students succeed. Only criticism I have is that her lectures weren't always very organized and her grading criteria for assignments/discussion posts were unclear. For exams just memorize!

I took this class as an elective but it turned out to be one of my hardest courses of the entire semester. I understand it was her first time teaching but she needs to realize not everyone taking religious studies courses wants to do a PhD in it ... definitely a hard grader although she is quite passionate, knowledgeable and hilarious at times..

I learned so much from Professor Fords lectures! The lectures are essential to passing this class, the course is content-heavy, but she will be able to guide you through if you make an effort to reach out! As an accounting student, I thought this course was well structured and well taught.
